The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation at a Glance
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Nation Briefs
              
	Bail ruling       
	 Mumbai, Oct. 26 (PTI): A person arrested in connection with a bailable offence must be released on personal bond after seven days in custody, even if he/she is not able to furnish regular bail, Bombay High Court has said.     
	If the accused remains in jail for more than a week, the jails in-charge will have to compensate the person out of his own pocket, the court said.     
	IAS dowry    
	 Jaipur (PTI): Shalini Agarwal, an IAS officer from Gujarat, has accused her husband, also a civil servant, of dowry harassment and torture. A police team was sent to Gujarat to question Rahul Gupta, a district development officer in Anand, an official said.     
	Terror arrest     
	 Jammu (PTI): Two suspected members of the Lashkar-e-Toiba, including a Class XII student, were arrested on Saturday in Jammu, officers said. The arrests were made at Ragunath Bazaar, in the heart of the city. Police seized ammunition and two letter pads allegedly belonging to a Lashkar commander.     
	Molest cuffs    
	 Aruppukkotai, TN (PTI): A man was sentenced to seven years in jail on Saturday for sexually assaulting a 13-year-old girl in Virudhunagar district. Ravichandran, 30, had assaulted the girl, a Class VII student, on her way to school. A complaint had been lodged at an all-women police station.     
	Flood alert     
	 Nagercoil (PTI): Flood alerts have been sounded in areas downstream of Pechiparai and Chittar dams after a rise in water level following heavy rain in Kanyakumari district for 10 days. People living in low-lying areas have been asked to move to safer places, an official said.     
	Rice seizure    
	 Dindigul (PTI): More than 125 bags of rice, meant for distribution under the PDS, were seized and six persons arrested near Dindigul on Saturday. A special police squad found 30 rice bags being illegally transported in a lorry during a routine check.                                                                                                                                                                  
